e Canadian welfare state from the U.S. version make a difference in protecting Canadian workers from the hardships that burden low-wage workers in the United States. Differences That Matter, which is filled with first-person accounts, ends with policy recommendations and a call for grassroots community organizing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aPovertyxGovernment policyzCanada. 0aPovertyxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aWorking poorzCanada. 0aWorking poorzUnited States. 4aBusiness (General). 4aLabor History. 4aSociology & Social Science.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171125140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501711251423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501711251/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles